{"title_page": "Willie Smith (footballer, born 1943)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2017}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Willie Smith\n|image          = \n|caption        = \n|fullname       = William Smith<ref>{{Hugman|18448|accessdate=12 March 2017}}</ref>\n|birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1943|12|6|df=y}}\n|birth_place    = [[Glasgow]], Scotland\n|death_date     = \n|death_place    = \n|height         = \n|position       = [[Wing half]], [[inside left]]\n|youthyears1    = {{0|0000}}\u20131960\n|youthclubs1    = [[Blantyre Celtic F.C.|Blantyre Celtic]]\n|years1 =  1960\u20131963        \n|clubs1 = [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]                                  \n|caps1 =   0  \n|goals1 = 0\n|years2 = 1963\u20131965 \n|clubs2 = [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]]                           \n|caps2 = 25   \n|goals2 = 0\n|years3 =  \n|clubs3 = [[Hastings United F.C. (1948)|Hastings United]] \n|caps3 =  \n|goals3 = \n}}\n'''William''' '''Smith''' (born 6 December 1943) is a Scottish retired professional [[association football|football]] [[wing half]] who played in the [[The Football League|Football League]] for [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]].\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Early years ===\nBorn in [[Glasgow]], Smith began his career as an [[inside left]] with junior club [[Blantyre Celtic F.C.|Blantyre Celtic]] before securing a move to [[Scottish Football League First Division|Scottish League First Division]] club [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] in 1960.<ref name=\"celticwiki\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.thecelticwiki.com/page/Players+Who+Never+Played+a+Game++++M+-+Z |title=Players Who Never Played a Game M \u2013 Z |website=thecelticwiki.com |access-date=15 June 2015}}</ref> He failed to appear for the first team and departed [[Celtic Park]] in 1963.<ref name=\"celticwiki\" /><ref name=\"Timeless\">{{Cite book |title=Timeless Bees: Brentford F.C. Who's Who 1920\u20132006 |last=Haynes |first=Graham |last2=Coumbe |first2=Frank |publisher=Yore Publications |year=2006 |isbn=978-0955294914 |location=Harefield |page=150}}</ref>\n\n=== Brentford ===\nSmith moved to [[Football in England|England]] and was recruited by [[Football League Third Division|Third Division]] club [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford's]] Scottish manager [[Malky McDonald]] in June 1963.<ref name=\"Timeless\" /> Playing as a [[wing half]], Smith made something of a breakthrough into the first team during the [[1963\u201364 Brentford F.C. season|1963\u201364]] season and made 18 appearances.<ref name=\"White\">{{Cite book |title=100 Years Of Brentford |publisher=Brentford FC |year=1989 |isbn=0951526200 |editor-last=White |editor-first=Eric |pages=388\u2013388}}</ref> Over the course of the following two seasons, Smith lost his place to [[Mel Scott]] and made just 12 appearances.<ref name=\"Timeless\" /><ref name=\"White\" /> He was mostly confined to the [[Brentford Reserves|reserves]] and won the [[London Challenge Cup]] with the team in 1965.<ref name=\"AZBees\">{{Cite book |title=A-Z Of Bees: Brentford Encyclopaedia |last=Haynes |first=Graham |date=1998 |publisher=Yore Publications |isbn=1 874427 57 7 |page=82}}</ref> Smith departed [[Griffin Park]] at the end of the [[1965\u201366 Brentford F.C. season|1965\u201366]] and made 30 appearances for the club.<ref name=\"Timeless\" />\n\n=== Hastings United ===\nAfter his release from Brentford, Smith dropped into [[Non-League football|non-league football]] and signed for [[Southern Football League|Southern League]] First Division club [[Hastings United F.C. (1948)|Hastings United]] during the 1966 off-season.<ref name=\"Timeless\" /> He helped the club to a second-place finish in the [[1966\u201367 Southern Football League|1966\u201367]] season, which secured promotion to the Premier Division.<ref name=\"Timeless\" />\n\n== Honours ==\n'''Brentford Reserves'''\n* [[London Challenge Cup]]: [[1964\u201365 Brentford F.C. season|1964\u201365]]<ref name=\"AZBees\" />\n\n== Career statistics ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Club\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Season\n! colspan=\"3\" |League\n! colspan=\"2\" |FA Cup\n! colspan=\"2\" |League Cup\n! colspan=\"2\" |Total\n|-\n!Division\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]]\n|[[1963\u201364 Brentford F.C. season|1963\u201364]]<ref name=\"White\" />\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Football League Third Division|Third Division]]\n|13\n|0\n|1\n|0\n|4\n|0\n|18\n|0\n|-\n|[[1964\u201365 Brentford F.C. season|1964\u201365]]<ref name=\"White\" />\n|7\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|7\n|0\n|-\n|[[1965\u201366 Brentford F.C. season|1965\u201366]]<ref name=\"White\" />\n|5\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|5\n|0\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" |Career total\n!25\n!0\n!1\n!0\n!4\n!0\n!30\n!0\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Smith, Willie}}\n[[Category:1943 births]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Glasgow]]\n[[Category:Scottish footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football inside forwards]]\n[[Category:Brentford F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Blantyre Celtic F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Celtic F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Hastings United F.C. (1948) players]]\n[[Category:Southern Football League players]]\n[[Category:Association football wing halves]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Scottish Junior Football Association players]]\n\n\n{{Scotland-footy-midfielder-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2017}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Willie Smith\n|image          = \n|caption        = \n|fullname       = William Smith<ref>{{Hugman|18448|accessdate=12 March 2017}}</ref>\n|birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1943|12|6|df=y}}\n|birth_place    = [[Glasgow]], Scotland\n|death_date     = \n|death_place    = \n|height         = \n|position       = [[Wing half]], [[inside left]]\n|youthyears1    = {{0|0000}}\u20131960\n|youthclubs1    = [[Blantyre Celtic F.C.|Blantyre Celtic]]\n|years1 =  1960\u20131963        \n|clubs1 = [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]                                  \n|caps1 =   0  \n|goals1 = 0\n|years2 = 1963\u20131965 \n|clubs2 = [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]]                           \n|caps2 = 25   \n|goals2 = 0\n|years3 =  \n|clubs3 = [[Hastings United F.C. (1948)|Hastings United]] \n|caps3 =  \n|goals3 = \n}}\n'''William''' '''Smith''' (born 6 December 1943) is a retired Scottish professional [[association football|football]] [[wing half]] who played in the [[The Football League|Football League]] for [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]].\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Early years ===\nBorn in [[Glasgow]], Smith began his career as an [[inside left]] with junior club [[Blantyre Celtic F.C.|Blantyre Celtic]] before securing a move to [[Scottish Football League First Division|Scottish League First Division]] club [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] in 1960.<ref name=\"celticwiki\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.thecelticwiki.com/page/Players+Who+Never+Played+a+Game++++M+-+Z |title=Players Who Never Played a Game M \u2013 Z |website=thecelticwiki.com |access-date=15 June 2015}}</ref> He failed to appear for the first team and departed [[Celtic Park]] in 1963.<ref name=\"celticwiki\" /><ref name=\"Timeless\">{{Cite book |title=Timeless Bees: Brentford F.C. Who's Who 1920\u20132006 |last=Haynes |first=Graham |last2=Coumbe |first2=Frank |publisher=Yore Publications |year=2006 |isbn=978-0955294914 |location=Harefield |page=150}}</ref>\n\n=== Brentford ===\nSmith moved to [[Football in England|England]] and was recruited by [[Football League Third Division|Third Division]] club [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford's]] [[Scotland|Scottish]] manager [[Malky McDonald]] in June 1963.<ref name=\"Timeless\" /> Playing as a [[wing half]], Smith made something of a breakthrough into the first team during the [[1963\u201364 Brentford F.C. season|1963\u201364]] season and made 18 appearances.<ref name=\"White\">{{Cite book |title=100 Years Of Brentford |publisher=Brentford FC |year=1989 |isbn=0951526200 |editor-last=White |editor-first=Eric |pages=388\u2013388}}</ref> Over the course of the following two seasons, Smith lost his place to [[Mel Scott]] and made just 12 appearances.<ref name=\"Timeless\" /><ref name=\"White\" /> He was mostly confined to the [[Brentford Reserves|reserves]] and won the [[London Challenge Cup]] with the team in 1965.<ref name=\"AZBees\">{{Cite book |title=A-Z Of Bees: Brentford Encyclopaedia |last=Haynes |first=Graham |date=1998 |publisher=Yore Publications |isbn=1 874427 57 7 |page=82}}</ref> Smith departed [[Griffin Park]] at the end of the [[1965\u201366 Brentford F.C. season|1965\u201366]] and made 30 appearances for the club.<ref name=\"Timeless\" />\n\n=== Hastings United ===\nAfter his release from Brentford, Smith dropped into [[Non-League football|non-league football]] and signed for [[Southern Football League|Southern League]] First Division club [[Hastings United F.C. (1948)|Hastings United]] during the 1966 off-season.<ref name=\"Timeless\" /> He helped the club to a second-place finish in the [[1966\u201367 Southern Football League|1966\u201367]] season, which secured promotion to the Premier Division.<ref name=\"Timeless\" />\n\n== Honours ==\n'''Brentford Reserves'''\n* [[London Challenge Cup]]: [[1964\u201365 Brentford F.C. season|1964\u201365]]<ref name=\"AZBees\" />\n\n== Career statistics ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Club\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Season\n! colspan=\"3\" |League\n! colspan=\"2\" |FA Cup\n! colspan=\"2\" |League Cup\n! colspan=\"2\" |Total\n|-\n!Division\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]]\n|[[1963\u201364 Brentford F.C. season|1963\u201364]]<ref name=\"White\" />\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Football League Third Division|Third Division]]\n|13\n|0\n|1\n|0\n|4\n|0\n|18\n|0\n|-\n|[[1964\u201365 Brentford F.C. season|1964\u201365]]<r